+A tool for copying and organizing master calibration frames into a structured library.
+
+## Overview
+
+This tool copies master calibration frames (bias, dark, flat) from a source directory to a destination library, organizing them by frame type and camera configuration. It reads FITS metadata to determine the appropriate destination path and filename.
+
+## Usage
+
+```powershell
+python -m ap_move_calibration.move_calibration <source_dir> <dest_dir> [--debug] [--dryrun] [--no-overwrite] [--help]
+```
+
+Options:
+- `source_dir`: Source directory containing master calibration files
+- `dest_dir`: Destination directory for organized calibration library
+- `--debug`: Enable debug output
+- `--dryrun`: Perform dry run without copying files
+- `--no-overwrite`: Fail if destination files already exist (default: overwrite)
+- `--help`: Show help message and exit
+
+## Installation
+
+### From Source (Development)
+
+```powershell
+make install-dev
+```
+
+This installs the package in editable mode along with all dependencies (including `ap-common` from git) and development tools.
+
+### From Git Repository (One-liner)
+
+```powershell
+pip install git+https://github.com/jewzaam/ap-move-calibration.git
+```
+
+This installs the package directly from the GitHub repository without requiring a local checkout.
+
+### Uninstallation
+
+```powershell
+make uninstall
+```
+
+## How It Works
+
+1. Scans `source_dir` recursively for master calibration files (.xisf, .fits)
+2. Reads FITS headers to extract metadata (frame type, camera, temperature, gain, etc.)
+3. Organizes files by type into the destination library:
+   - **BIAS**: `dest_dir/BIAS/{camera}/{filename}`
+   - **DARK**: `dest_dir/DARK/{camera}/{filename}`
+   - **FLAT**: `dest_dir/FLAT/{camera}/{optic}/DATE_{date}/{filename}`
+4. Generates descriptive filenames from metadata properties
+
+## Output Structure
+
+```
+dest_dir/
+├── BIAS/
+│   └── {camera}/
+│       └── masterBias_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}_SET-TEMP_{temp}.xisf
+├── DARK/
+│   └── {camera}/
+│       └── masterDark_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}_SET-TEMP_{temp}_EXPOSURE_{seconds}.xisf
+└── FLAT/
+    └── {camera}/
+        └── {optic}/
+            └── DATE_{date}/
+                └── masterFlat_GAIN_{gain}_OFFSET_{offset}_READOUTM_{mode}_SET-TEMP_{temp}_FILTER_{filter}.xisf
+```
+
+## Examples
+
+### Basic Copy
+
+```powershell
+python -m ap_move_calibration.move_calibration D:\Masters D:\CalibrationLibrary
+```
+
+### Dry Run
+
+```powershell
+python -m ap_move_calibration.move_calibration D:\Masters D:\CalibrationLibrary --dryrun
+```
+
+### Debug Mode
+
+```powershell
+python -m ap_move_calibration.move_calibration D:\Masters D:\CalibrationLibrary --debug
+```
+
+### Prevent Overwriting
+
+```powershell
+python -m ap_move_calibration.move_calibration D:\Masters D:\CalibrationLibrary --no-overwrite
+```
+
+## Required FITS Keywords
+
+Master calibration files must have the `IMAGETYP` keyword set to one of:
+- `MASTER BIAS`
+- `MASTER DARK`
+- `MASTER FLAT`
